The paper discusses a simple algorithm for computing a matching on a graph that can be adapted to various models of computation, including PRAM, External Memory, MapReduce, and distributed memory models. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to parallel and distributed computing, such as cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.Distributed (Distributed Computing).
